**architecture-diagrams.drawio**

```markdown
# Architecture Diagrams (draw.io)

This is a placeholder file for your draw.io diagram. In the actual `.drawio` file (which is XML-based), you would draw these diagrams visually.

## Recommended Diagrams to Create in draw.io:

### 1. Simple Startup Architecture
- Users → App API → Database

### 2. Horizontal Scaling + Load Balancer
- Users → Load Balancer → [App1, App2, App3] → Database

### 3. Add Redis Cache
- App → Redis → Database

### 4. Database Read Replicas
- Primary DB → [Replica1, Replica2, Replica3]

### 5. Kafka Queue
- API → Kafka Topic → Worker Group → DB

### 6. Sharding
- App → Shard Router → [DB1(Shard1), DB2(Shard2), DB3(Shard3)]

### 7. Complete Final Architecture (The one in high-traffic-system-design.md)
- Users → Load Balancer → [App1, App2, App3] → Redis → Kafka → Workers → Sharded DBs (with CDN on the side)

## How to use this file:

1. Open [draw.io](https://app.diagrams.net/)
2. Click "Open Existing Diagram"
3. Select this `architecture-diagrams.drawio` file
4. Draw the diagrams above using the shapes palette
5. Save (it will update the XML content automatically)

## Alternative: Use Mermaid (for markdown)

If you prefer code-based diagrams, add this to your markdown files:

\`\`\`mermaid
graph TD
    Users --> LB[Load Balancer]
    LB --> App1
    LB --> App2
    LB --> App3
    App1 --> Redis
    App2 --> Redis
    App3 --> Redis
    Redis --> Kafka
    Kafka --> Workers
    Workers --> DB1[(Shard 1)]
    Workers --> DB2[(Shard 2)]
\`\`\`